properties.headline: Blizzard Warning issued February 17 at 4:50AM AKST until February 18 at 6:00AM AKST by NWS Anchorage, AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Blizzard conditions occurring. Additional snow
accumulations of 2 to 5 inches. Winds gusting up to 45 mph.
Visibility of one quarter mile or less.

* WHERE...Kuskokwim Delta west of Bethel. Expect the worst
conditions along the Kuskokwim Delta coast.

* WHEN...Through 6 AM AKST Tuesday.

* IMPACTS...Areas of blowing snow could significantly reduce
visibility.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Blizzard conditions will continue for the
Kuskokwim Delta coast this morning. Visibilities are one
quarter mile from Kipnuk to Hooper Bay at times in heavy and
blowing snow. The strongest winds will diminish this afternoon,
but expect snow and blowing snow to continue through the
overnight hours.
properties.instruction:
A Blizzard Warning means severe winter weather conditions are
expected or occurring. Falling and blowing snow with strong winds
and poor visibilities are likely. This will lead to whiteout
conditions, making travel very hazardous. If you must travel,
have a winter survival kit with you.If you get stranded, stay
with your vehicle.

NWSheadline: BLIZZARD WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 AM AKST TUESDAY WEST OF BETHEL
